A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Local Government – Local Personnel – Leave With Pay
3 FOR the purpose of establishing that an employee of a governmental unit of a county or a
4 municipality may be entitled to disaster service leave with pay under certain
5 circumstances; authorizing certain governmental units to waive certain
6 requirements for disaster service leave; authorizing a governmental unit of a county
7 or a municipality to provide certain leave with pay under certain circumstances; and
8 generally relating to disaster service leave and leave with pay for employees of
9 counties and municipalities in the State.
10 BY adding to
11 Article – Local Government
12 Section 1–207 and 1–208
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2013 Volume and 2024 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Local Government
18 1–207.
19 (A) THIS SECTION APPLIES TO ALL EMPLOYEES OF A GOVERNMENTAL UNIT
20 OF A COUNTY OR A MUNICIPALITY IN THE STATE.
21 (B) ON REQUEST, AN EMPLOYEE SUBJECT TO THIS SECTION MAY BE
22 ENTITLED TO DISASTER SERVICE LEAVE WITH PAY IF:
